1
00:00:14,725 --> 00:00:18,487
♪Allergic to fast-food love,
even if it's too naive♪

2
00:00:18,562 --> 00:00:22,162
♪Just like a hug needs
the right body heat♪

3
00:00:22,287 --> 00:00:25,437
♪Your "same here" carries
a touch of resolve♪

4
00:00:25,862 --> 00:00:29,412
♪Pack my bags, we can set off right now♪

5
00:00:29,637 --> 00:00:33,112
♪The future is a wondrous,
unknown adventure♪

6
00:00:33,250 --> 00:00:36,712
♪The journey itself is what
truly matters before the destination♪

7
00:00:36,787 --> 00:00:40,975
♪Those moments together
are what bind us strongest♪

8
00:00:41,025 --> 00:00:42,612
♪Connect♪

9
00:00:42,625 --> 00:00:43,275
♪Let's go!♪

10
00:00:43,612 --> 00:00:47,137
♪Leave worries behind
in yesterday's sentimentality♪

11
00:00:47,237 --> 00:00:50,675
♪Today, no dwelling
on negative emotions♪

12
00:00:50,750 --> 00:00:53,450
♪Tomorrow holds more luck♪

13
00:00:53,450 --> 00:00:55,262
♪Together we'll create moving melodies♪

14
00:00:55,262 --> 00:00:58,199
♪The future begins to take shape♪

15
00:00:59,075 --> 00:01:02,375
=Love In A Secret=
(I Just Want to Drown With You)

16
00:01:02,675 --> 00:01:06,275
=Episode 2=

17
00:01:09,187 --> 00:01:10,587
Man, you're here.

18
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:12,200
Let me introduce them.

19
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:13,080
This is Mr. Lu.

20
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:15,560
Hi, Mr. Lu.

21
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:17,680
I've heard about you from my mother.

22
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:19,480
We finally meet today.

23
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:20,840
Zhu,

24
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:21,960
address your brother.

25
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:34,560
Hi, younger sister.

26
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:01,720
Man, Mr. Lu and I have to
entertain our clients later.

27
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:02,800
Send your sister home.

28
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:03,920
Mom, don't worry about it.

29
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:05,280
Let's go.

30
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:21,200
You knew who I was long ago, right?

31
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,960
Not that long ago, I suppose.

32
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:25,680
What are you doing?

33
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:26,680
I'm sending you home.

34
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:30,160
They already left.

35
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:31,920
Stop pretending.

36
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:34,240
You've been scheming to get close to me.

37
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:37,480
And, you even made up
a fairy tale just to deceive me.

38
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:39,200
What exactly are you up to?

39
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:47,080
I heard

40
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:50,480
that the daughter of the Lu family
was gentle and elegant.

41
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:54,120
But the real you

42
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,360
prove to be quite different.

43
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:04,560
Younger sister,

44
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,660
it seems like you're hiding something.

45
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,920
That's my business.

46
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:18,120
Mind your own business.

47
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:22,200
You!

48
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:26,920
Just you wait.

49
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:33,520
(The massive Ye family
pig-butchering scam has collapsed.)

50
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:35,360
(The chairman of Ye Group
took his own life.)

51
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,400
(Who can repay
the trillion-dollar debt for him?)

52
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:44,880
(Just like me, he harbors ulterior motives
toward the Lu family.)

53
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:53,320
Okay. Pick up the pace.

54
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:56,400
Miss.

55
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:57,880
This...

56
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,840
Come, take a look.

57
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:10,120
Zhu.

58
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:13,760
Why did you take this trash with you?

59
00:04:14,650 --> 00:04:15,560
How could you say that?

60
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:17,760
You're getting more and more unruly.

61
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:20,840
Zhu,

62
00:04:21,075 --> 00:04:22,337
from now on, Man will move in

63
00:04:22,337 --> 00:04:23,217
and live with us.

64
00:04:23,565 --> 00:04:24,525
You two

65
00:04:24,525 --> 00:04:25,925
must get along.

66
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,160
That's right. What about this?

67
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,240
You can take Man

68
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,360
around the house

69
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,480
and get an overview.

70
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:32,000
We'll head inside first.

71
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:43,640
How did you manage

72
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:45,560
to deceive my dad to bring you back?

73
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:47,640
How could you say something like this
to your elder brother, younger sister?

74
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:47,960
You!

75
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:48,560
What's wrong?

76
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,400
Are you upset?

77
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,720
I'm so elated.

78
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:53,920
Mr. Lu

79
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,080
told you to take me around the house.

80
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:57,160
Where are you taking me?

81
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:00,920
You can proceed by yourself.

82
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:02,440
I'm going to swim.

83
00:05:20,937 --> 00:05:22,240
Have you lost your mind?

84
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:23,400
It's only been a few moments,

85
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:24,660
yet I'm already missing you.

86
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:32,665
Man, what a coincidence.

87
00:05:34,137 --> 00:05:35,512
I missed you too.

88
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:09,560
Zhu,

89
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:12,560
your prank needs to get better.

90
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,600
Next time, it's my turn.

91
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:22,520
Just you wait!

92
00:06:28,525 --> 00:06:32,500
(Business Horizons)

93
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:35,720
Mom.

94
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,280
Here, have some.

95
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:42,160
You're still reading the interview
with Mr. Lu, huh?

96
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:43,520
I have to learn from him.

97
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,200
By the way, Mom,

98
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,600
I wish to work for Lu Group.

99
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,480
Can you...

100
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,600
That's what I thought too.

101
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,737
But you see,

102
00:06:53,737 --> 00:06:56,190
it's better for you to draw a line
with your father's matters.

103
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:58,687
You should learn
how to do business from Mr. Lu.

104
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:01,200
You're a part of the Lu family now.

105
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:03,400
You need to join
the company sooner or later.

106
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,400
Alright.

107
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:10,160
But there's no need to be impatient.

108
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,237
I'll try to think of something.

109
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,520
Okay.

110
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:14,840
Sleep early.

111
00:07:15,675 --> 00:07:16,555
Goodbye, Mom.

112
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:36,200
That's mine.

113
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,320
Don't touch it.

114
00:07:45,862 --> 00:07:46,902
What a coincidence.

115
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:49,800
You see, I like to steal from
other people the most.

116
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:52,760
You're shameless.

117
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:55,880
Where are you going?

118
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:57,490
Aren't you going
to join me for breakfast?

119
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:03,700
You guys are already here, huh?

120
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:04,880
Morning, Mom.

121
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,280
Morning, Mr. Lu.

122
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:12,375
Man,

123
00:08:12,437 --> 00:08:13,425
what type of books

124
00:08:13,425 --> 00:08:14,687
do you like to read usually?

125
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,960
I don't read that much.

126
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:18,080
But when I do, I read about
the principles of economics,

127
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:19,080
the wealth of nations,

128
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:20,200
currency wars, and so on.

129
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:24,320
That's great.

130
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:26,525
Man is very hardworking.

131
00:08:26,575 --> 00:08:27,320
What about this?

132
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:29,480
I'll lend you this book for now.

133
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,680
Thank you, Mr. Lu.

134
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:34,760
Zhu,

135
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,440
what books have you read lately?

136
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:39,840
I read a book called

137
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,200
"Meeting Him

138
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,960
Is A Risk I'm Willing to Lose."

139
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,560
What kind of book is that?

140
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:50,000
What is she talking about?

141
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:52,587
We're getting old.

142
00:08:52,587 --> 00:08:55,440
It's difficult for us to understand
the slang of youngsters nowadays.

143
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,880
There's a generation gap.

144
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,880
By the way,
since Man is new to the place,

145
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:02,287
I'll take him around
if we have nothing to do this afternoon.

146
00:09:02,287 --> 00:09:03,167
No need for that.

147
00:09:03,225 --> 00:09:04,800
We can just tell Zhu to take him around.

148
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:10,080
Take Man around after breakfast, okay?

149
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,680
I'm done.

150
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:19,900
You guys can enjoy your meal.

151
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:27,960
I'll take you "around" later,

152
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:30,160
Man.

153
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:36,040
That girl is so mischievous.

154
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,440
She's adorable.

155
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:42,560
Hello, Hua?

156
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:44,160
I'm bringing someone there tonight.

157
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:45,520
Help me intimidate him.

158
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,720
Who are you trying to prank this time?

159
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:49,040
You don't need to know.

160
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:51,040
Just find some extras for me
when the time comes.

161
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:52,600
I'll pay you double.

162
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:54,685
Got it, Goddess of Wealth.

163
00:10:02,212 --> 00:10:06,712
♪Bit by bit, I'll forget you♪

164
00:10:06,937 --> 00:10:10,725
♪Bit by bit, I'll erase the memories♪

165
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:14,975
♪From now on,
your image won't linger in my mind♪

166
00:10:14,975 --> 00:10:19,112
♪Nor will those fragments of the past♪

167
00:10:19,237 --> 00:10:23,012
♪Days will slowly drift away
like passing clouds♪

168
00:10:23,012 --> 00:10:26,787
♪I'll learn to stop
longing for what's gone♪

169
00:10:26,787 --> 00:10:29,062
♪The you in my memories♪

170
00:10:29,062 --> 00:10:31,075
♪Will fade from clarity♪

171
00:10:31,075 --> 00:10:36,512
♪How much longer must I wait to♪

172
00:10:38,075 --> 00:10:43,512
♪Forget you completely♪
